<p>
phpMyAdmin security announcement
</p>
<hr>
<p>
Announcement-ID: PMASA-2006-9<br />
Date: 2006-11-17<br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Summary</b>:<br />
Bad IP Allow/Deny checking
</p>
<p>
<b>Description</b>:<br />
We received a security advisory from Christian Schmidt, Peytz & Co. and we wish to thank him for his work.
<br />
<br />
It was possible to get around IP-based Allow/Deny checking by faking proxy headers.
</p>
<p>
<b>Severity</b>:<br />
We consider this vulnerability to be serious. 
</p>
<p>
<b>Affected versions</b>:<br />
Probably all versions to 2.9.1.
</p>
<p>
<b>Solution:</b><br />
Upgrade to phpMyAdmin 2.9.1.1 or newer.
</p>
<p>
For further information and in case of questions, please contact the
phpMyAdmin team. Our website is <a href="http://www.phpmyadmin.net">http://www.phpmyadmin.net/</a>.
</p>
